result.adr_address: 75 High St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 75 High St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: Maison Eric Kayser - Sai Ying Pun

reviews.text: Good coffee n sandwiches as usual. Nice friendly workers.
Great coffee and bakery goods. Went every day so must be good.

Great selection of bakery but need to buck up on customer service. Simply rude staff esp the hongkongese staff who started working when shop is newly open. I reckon shes been with Kayser for long time as seen her being so friendly with her colleagues. Maybe she should treat her customers the same. No acknowledgement / no eye contact when arriving at counter for payment. Just ramble on with total amount and off you go. Wonder if any basic training is given

Used to be quite good but at this price point, all i see are greasy soggy croissants, which is a disappointment.  Your staff seem very unmotivated and give off the air of "i dont give a f&ck"....i only see a downward spiral and closure at this rate
Probably the single most useful thing I’ve discovered in HK. Their grab and go sandwiches are delicious and a lifesaver when I’m short on time. And the dark chocolate cookie is phenomenal.
